Design Services

SoCQuest expertise lies in analog end to end solutions with a system level application. With Analog end solution perspective, we provide an extensive set of full‑flow IC design services focused on supporting semiconductor and systems companies in the delivery of analog Ips for SoC, ASIC or FPGA projects.  These services range from a full turnkey solution that delivers a production ready design, to sub‑system or IP block development, or having our engineers augment your existing design teams with specialist design, application or EDA tools expertise.

If you need design services or want to outsource a specific functional block, let us know. We have an experienced team that can help you to off‑load.

{/* Remaining sections stay as-is */}

Analog Design and Services

  • Amplifiers, Reference generation circuits
  • Power Management units (LDO, Buck-Boost Regulators)
  • Audio and Power Amplifiers
  • High speed serial links (Serializer/Deserializer)
  • Data converters
  • Clocking circuits , PLL and Clock Data Recovery (CDR) Calibration blocks

Analog and RF Layout

  • Layout services for Standard cells design enablement,
  • General Purpose IOs
  • ESD layout designs for HBM, CDM and MM
  • Layouts for TSMC, SS, GF foundry    nodes
  • DRC, LVS, PERC, DFM, Reliability like EMIR, Aging

Analog simulation Verification/Automation

  • Automation for full   corner cases coverage for blocks/IP
  • Mixes  signal, simulations with analog and digital
  • PVT simulations
  • Analog  Behavioral modeling
  • Hierarchical modeling   for every cell  to  lowest level of  primitive cell using  verilogAMS, verilogA, Verilog, VHDL,SystemVerilog
  • Behavioral model   at   IP/System level for early access of the  pin interface

Digital Frontend and Backend

RTL design​ and Verification

  • Robust RTL designs for smaller SOCs
  • Expertise in RTL designs across IPs, SOC and ASICs
  • Optimal design with reduces  area and power
  • Digital Verification of the RTL, Test coverage

Implementation and Physical Design

  • Synthesizing the netlist
  • Timing closures,  STA
  • Placement and routing
  • DFT
